juniRadiusProxyMIB.name: juniRadiusProxyMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

juniRadiusProxyMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@Juniper.net
juniRadiusProxyMIB.description: The RADIUS Proxy MIB for the Juniper Networks enterprise.

juniRadiusProxyUdpChecksum.name: juniRadiusProxyUdpChecksum
juniRadiusProxyUdpChecksum.description: Enables/disables the checksum calculations on RADIUS UDP packets.

juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgPortNumber.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgPortNumber
juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgPortNumber.description: The UDP port the RADIUS authentication proxy server will use. The server will first be created, if necessary. A value of 0 indicates the server should be deleted.

juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientTable.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientTable
juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientTable.description: The table listing the clients with which the RADIUS authentication proxy server shares a secret.

juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientEntry.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientEntry
juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientEntry.description: An entry (row) representing clients with which the RADIUS authentication proxy server shares a secret.

juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientAddress.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientAddress
juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientAddress.description: The IP Network Address of the RADIUS authentication proxy server's clients.

juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientMask.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientMask
juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientMask.description: The IP Network Address Mask of the RADIUS authentication proxy server's clients.

juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientKey.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientKey
juniRadiusAuthProxyCfgClientKey.description: The secret (RADIUS authenticator) used by the clients during exchanges with this authentication proxy server.

juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgPortNumber.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgPortNumber
juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgPortNumber.description: The UDP port the RADIUS accounting proxy server will use. The server will first be created, if necessary. A value of 0 indicates the server should be deleted.

juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientTable.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientTable
juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientTable.description: The table listing the clients with which the RADIUS accounting proxy server shares a secret.

juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientEntry.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientEntry
juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientEntry.description: An entry (row) representing clients with which the RADIUS accounting proxy server shares a secret.

juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientAddress.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientAddress
juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientAddress.description: The IP Network Address of the RADIUS accounting proxy server's clients.

juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientMask.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientMask
juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientMask.description: The IP Network Address Mask of the RADIUS accounting proxy server's clients.

juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientKey.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientKey
juniRadiusAcctProxyCfgClientKey.description: The secret (RADIUS authenticator) used by the clients during exchanges with this accounting proxy server.

juniRadiusProxyCompliance.name: juniRadiusProxyCompliance
juniRadiusProxyCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities implementing the JUNOSe RADIUS Proxy Server MIB functionality.

juniRadiusBasicProxyGroup.name: juniRadiusBasicProxyGroup
juniRadiusBasicProxyGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic management of RADIUS Proxy Servers.

juniRadiusAuthProxyGroup.name: juniRadiusAuthProxyGroup
juniRadiusAuthProxyGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of RADIUS Authentication Proxy Servers.

juniRadiusAcctProxyGroup.name: juniRadiusAcctProxyGroup
juniRadiusAcctProxyGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management of RADIUS Accounting Proxy Servers.
